Nikita Vitiugov vs Jan-Krzysztof Duda
Prague Chess Festival (Masters) (2019), Prague CZE, rd 7, Mar-13 
Sicilian Defense: Najdorf Variation (B90)

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cd4 4. Nd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. a4 g6 7. Be2 Bg7 8. Be3 Nc6 9. O-O O-O 10. Qd2 Nd4 11. Bd4 Be6 12. a5 Rc8 13. Ra4 Rc6 14. f4 Qd7 15. Rb4 Rfc8 16. Bd3 Bc4 17. h3 Bd3 18. Qd3 e5 19. Be3 ef4 20. Bf4 Qc7 21. Kh1 b5 22. ab6 Rb6 23. Rb6 Qb6 24. Bd6 Qb2 25. Nd5 Rc2 26. Ba3 Qb5 27. Nf6 Bf6 28. Qb5 ab5 29. Rf6 b4 30. Bb4 Rc1 31. Kh2 Rc4 32. Rb6 Re4 33. Bc3 Re8 34. Bf6 h6 35. h4 Kh7 36. Rd6 Re4 37. g3 Re2 38. Kg1 Re3 39. Rd8 g5 40. h5 Rg3 41. Kf2 g4 42. Rh8#

To those of you who read the description: You are an excellent subscriber! :)

The Masters is a 10-player round-robin tournament organized by Nov√Ω Bor Chess Club, taking place from 6-15 March in the Hotel Don Giovanni in Prague, Czech Republic.

Players receive 90 minutes for 40 moves, followed by 30 minutes to the end of the game, with a 30-second increment starting from move one. Official website: www.praguechessfestival.com
